               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371127-name-256" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18371127-name-256" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371127-name-256" type="surname" value="DAWSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371127-name-256" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES DAWSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am clerk at Cotton's when. On the 21st of October I received 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., on this bill, and it has been altered to 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., since.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Are you quite certain you. only received 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.,? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I cannot tell from whom—the only difference between this bill and the money is 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—there is a good deal of business one at one wharf—we have to go in one way, and out another—net from the street; but the carts have to make a small circuit to go out.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371127-name-257" type="witnessName">
